### Phase 11 — Consolidated Smoke + Security Test Suite
### Run via VS Code REST Client or any HTTP client.
### Requires DB running (docker compose up -d).
### Requires one ADMIN user and one USER user.
###
### Setup:
###   1. docker compose up -d
###   2. npx prisma migrate dev --name init
###   3. npm run dev
###   4. Register two users via /api/auth/register
###   5. Get JWT tokens via next-auth (or manually set below)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@adminToken = <ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN>
@userToken = <USER_JWT_TOKEN>
@nonexistentId = 000000000000000000000000000000

### ==========================================
### 1. HEALTH CHECKS
### ==========================================

### 1a. Health endpoint returns ok
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health
// Expected: 200 { "ok": true, "service": "selflearn-ai", "version": "0.1.0" }

### 1b. Landing page loads
GET {{baseUrl}}/
// Expected: 200 text/html

### 1c. Login page loads
GET {{baseUrl}}/login
// Expected: 200 text/html

### ==========================================
### 2. AUTH TESTS
### ==========================================

### 2a. Unauthenticated chat fails
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat
Content-Type: application/json
{ "messages": [{ "role": "user", "content": "hello" }] }
// Expected: 401 { "error": "Authentication required." }

### 2b. Unauthenticated memories fails
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/memories
// Expected: 401 { "error": "Authentication required." }

### 2c. Unauthenticated conversations fails
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/conversations
// Expected: 401 { "error": "Authentication required." }

### 2d. Unauthenticated feedback fails
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json
{ "conversationId": "any", "messageId": "any", "type": "THUMBS_UP" }
// Expected: 401 { "error": "Authentication required." }

### 2e. Unauthenticated learning fails
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/learning/candidates
// Expected: 401 { "error": "Authentication required." }

### ==========================================
### 3. RATE LIMITING TESTS
### ==========================================

### 3a. Rapid register requests trigger rate limit (5/hr)
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register 6x in quick succession
# Expected on 6th: 429 { "error": "Too many requests. Please try again later." }

### 3b. Rapid chat requests trigger rate limit (30/min)
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat 31x with valid auth in quick succession
# Expected on 31st: 429

### ==========================================
### 4. SENSITIVE DATA TESTS
### ==========================================

### 4a. Secret-like memory rejected
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/memories
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
{ "text": "My API key is sk-abc123def456ghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz" }
// Expected: 400 { "error": "Text contains sensitive content and cannot be stored." }

### 4b. Password-like candidate rejected
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/learning/candidates
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
{ "text": "The password is P@ssw0rd123", "sensitivity": "LOW" }
// Expected: 400 { "error": "Candidate contains sensitive content..." }

### 4c. Password-like feedback correction rejected
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
{ "conversationId": "{{convId}}", "messageId": "{{msgId}}", "type": "CORRECTION", "correction": "My password is MyP@ssw0rd123" }
// Expected: 400 { "error": "Correction contains sensitive content..." }

### ==========================================
### 5. PROMPT INJECTION TESTS
### ==========================================

### 5a. Web source "ignore all instructions" (verified via code review)
# Web content wrapped in <web_search_results> with preamble
# AI sees: "The following information was retrieved from web search..."
# Content is reference data, not system instructions

### 5b. Memory "reveal system prompt" (verified via code review)
# Memory content wrapped in <user_memory_context>
# AI sees: "The following memories may be relevant. Use them only if helpful."

### 5c. Feedback "change system prompt" (verified via code review)
# Feedback corrections are stored in DB only, never sent to LLM

### ==========================================
### 6. INPUT VALIDATION TESTS
### ==========================================

### 6a. Oversized chat message rejected (4000 chars)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
{ "messages": [{ "role": "user", "content": "x" }}"
// Expected: 400

### 6b. Oversized memory rejected (5000 chars)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/memories
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
{ "text": "x" }
// Set text to 5001 chars
// Expected: 400

### 6c. Invalid role rejected
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{someUserId}}/role
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
{ "role": "SUPER_ADMIN" }
// Expected: 400 { "error": "Role must be ADMIN or USER." }

### ==========================================
### 7. ADMIN ACCESS CONTROL
### ==========================================

### 7a. USER blocked from admin
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/health
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
// Expected: 403 { "error": "Forbidden. Admin access required." }

### 7b. ADMIN allowed
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/health
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
// Expected: 200 { "status": "healthy", ... }

### 7c. Invalid memory id returns 404
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/memories/nonexistent-id
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
// Expected: 404 { "error": "Memory not found." }

### ==========================================
### 8. SECURITY HEADERS
### ==========================================

### 8a. X-Frame-Options is set
GET {{baseUrl}}/
// Expected header: X-Frame-Options: DENY

### 8b. X-Content-Type-Options is set
GET {{baseUrl}}/
// Expected header: X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff

### 8c. Referrer-Policy is set
GET {{baseUrl}}/
// Expected header: Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin

### ==========================================
### 9. EXISTING FUNCTIONALITY — MANUAL TESTS
### ==========================================

### 9a. Register new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json
{ "email": "test-user@example.com", "password": "TestP@ssword123", "name": "Test User" }
// Expected: 201 { "ok": true }

### 9b. Health check works without auth
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health
// Expected: 200 { "ok": true }
